ObAgent: uncertain.

Analysis: application JDBC and remoteprocess latencies are high and db_003 DbTime and AIOS spike sharply while DB CPU is low — this points to DB-side IO/queueing or connection saturation, not plain network loss/delay or CPU. To disambiguate, check:
- whether_is_abnormal_metric(db_003, "Session_pct" / "Active_sessions" / "Current_connections") to detect connection-limit saturation;
- whether_is_abnormal_metric(db_003, "DB I/O latency" / "Disk read latency" / "I/O queue length") to confirm IO stalls;
- whether_is_abnormal_metric(os_022, "net.retransmits" or interface tx/rx errors) or run a collect_trace on docker -> os_022 -> db_003 to see time spent in network vs DB execution.
JudgeAgent: No - The agents finished as 'uncertain' and only suggested storage I/O delays affecting db_003 and os_021. That hypothesis is outside the closed set of allowed anomaly types, no single component/type was definitively selected, and no committed exact start minute for a chosen root cause was provided (though db_003 DbTime spiked at 2020-05-26 02:37:00). Therefore the root cause was not found.

